The health ingredients market is segmented into various categories to cater to the diverse needs of consumers. Vitamins form a significant part of this market, with essential nutrients like vitamin C, D, and E being in high demand due to their immune-boosting properties. Minerals such as calcium, magnesium, and iron are also crucial in supporting overall health and wellness. Probiotics have gained popularity for their benefits to gut health and digestion. Proteins, especially plant-based ones, are sought after for muscle building and weight management. Omega-3 fatty acids are essential for heart health and brain function. Plant extracts with antioxidant properties are used in natural health supplements, and the category of 'Others' includes a wide range of ingredients like fiber, amino acids, and collagen, each offering unique health advantages.

